Peter Dada, Akure The meeting between members of the Miyetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association of Nigeria and members of the Nigeria Governors Forum has started. Some of the governors in attendance include Ondo, Osun, Ekiti, Oyo, and Jigawa, and Kebbi states. In his welcome remarks, the chairman of the Nigeria Governors’ Forum and Governor of Ekiti State, Dr Kayode Fayemi, said the meeting was called to resolve the issue of insecurity in the South-West. [VIDEO] Sagamu-Benin Exp: Victims lament after herdsmen kidnap attempt He explained that the order pronounced by Governor Akeredolu was misconstrued by the media, particularly, the social media. He noted that Akeredolu had not ordered the Fulani to leave Ondo State. Fayemi said, “Many members of MACBAN were born in the South-West. So, Akeredolu cannot ask Fulani to vacate Ondo State. The area concerned is the forest reserves and it is about registration and also to work in line with the law. YOU MAY ALSO LIKE: Criminalising Fulani herdsmen is fishing for trouble —Buhari’s aide, Onochie “What we are after is the criminals, not Fulani herdsmen, criminals are criminals irrespective of their ethnic group.” Details later…